      "writtenOn": "2021-01-08T17:57:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks like this type really does two fairly different things:\n- make a new owned Variable with a given name and type\n- look up an existing Variable in the symbol table by name and provide a DSL reference to it\n\nI guess I would need to see how it is used in practice, but I\u0027m wondering if these are really the same thing? Do we really need both things in the same class? Even if we conceptually need a \"Variable\" class, could there be a base class with two subclasses for each distinct mode?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 21,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 35,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "14ce349c6e788dc3ef00776f7c050a786911be69",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
