        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-08T17:57:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is a default value that gives all variables the same name useful/a good idea? Seems like a footgun to me.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 41,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "14ce349c6e788dc3ef00776f7c050a786911be69",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae1fc453_4ef8ebbc",
        "filename": "src/sksl/dsl/DSLVar.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-08T19:50:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It works because of mangling. The default value exists because you already have to name the variable in C++ (\u0027Var foo(kInt)\u0027), the SkSL name only actually matters if you\u0027re looking at the resulting shader code (which clients likely won\u0027t be doing), and it\u0027s kind of annoying to have to specify the name twice (\u0027Var foo(kInt, \"foo\")\u0027). I\u0027ve added a comment to clarify.",
      "parentUuid": "f17f907f_9659f7fe",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 41,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "14ce349c6e788dc3ef00776f7c050a786911be69",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5bac2cb4_8ee3dffa",
        "filename": "src/sksl/dsl/DSLVar.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-08T17:57:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How often do we think clients will want to pass anything other than a quoted string for their variable names? I suspect it might be sufficient just to use `const char*` here and require the caller to pass in a string that will be stay fixed in place for the lifetime of the DSLVar (which probably isn\u0027t that long of a lifetime?).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "14ce349c6e788dc3ef00776f7c050a786911be69",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
